  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "R/jKCVVo9H22Iw+9VXj8jJngtiI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Shape of live collaboration\n\n- **Drive-level first, doc-level second.** Start with \"collaborate on this whole drive\" -- covers `ADD_FOLDER`, `MOVE_NODE`, and per-doc ops. Narrow to doc-level in a second pass using a tighter ACT grantee chain.\n- **Per-user op feeds + collab manifest.** Each collaborator writes ops to their own feed, because the Swarm constraint is that only the owner can write. A **collaboration manifest**, ACT-gated, lists participants and targets. Each collaborator reads every other collaborator's feeds.\n- **ACT gates read access.** Removing a participant rebuilds the ACT chain via `patchGrantees`.\n- **GSOC `op-committed` pings** replace the polling timer for active collabs. Debounced ~300 ms so a burst of ops triggers one pull, not one per op.\n- **Signatures already preserved** end-to-end (shipped 2026-04-17), so toolbar history shows the real author of every revision.\n\n## Build order\n\n1. Adapter plumbing\n2. Collab manifest + ACT\n3. SwarmChannel peer-feed registration\n4. GSOC pings\n5. Collaborate tab\n6. Invitation card\n7. Toolbar history auto-refresh\n8. Doc-level scope\n\nSee `live-collaboration-design.md` for detail.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
    }
  },
